    "This insight, at least in principle, guarantees that our algorithm will eventually converge to an optimal policy (with enough iterations) whereas ArCHer provides no such guarantees.",
    "Another important difference lies in the simplicity of our method.",
    "ArCHer employs TD learning and optimizes multiple critic networks (Q, V, and baseline networks), which often necessitates additional tricks and extensive hyperparameter tuning to ensure stability.",
    "In contrast, our algorithm can be implemented in two straightforward phases: a supervised Q-evaluation step, followed by PPO.",
    "POAD (Wen et al., 2024) is an orthogonal approach that extends PPO by decomposing actions into groups of tokens rather than individual tokens."
